  "text_preview": "ASL avocado ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► American Sign Language: \"avocado\" Lately the sign I've seen going around in 2018 for AVOCADO is to mime the twisting of the avocado halves. (You know how your slice an avocado then twist it to separate the two halves. Just pretend you are holding an avocado and twist it.) In a message dated 4/26/2005 8:25:29 AM Pacific Daylight Time, ____________@uni-tuebingen.de writes: Dear Bill, For a few weeks, I have been searching the net for information about ASL-- to teach it to my binational German and USA) children. while I enjoy procrastinating from my work and learning from your website, I found the signing time video being exciting for my three year old daughter and somewhat interesting to my 1 year old son. Now, my daughter"
}
